  <brief_title>A Crossover Study in the Treatment of Patients With COPD</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Dey</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Dey</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the efficacy of Formoterol Fumarate Inhalation
      Solution (FFIS) 20 mcg BID to CombiventÂ® Inhalation Aerosol [2 inhalations from metered dose
      inhaler (MDI)of 18 mcg ipratropium bromide and 103 mcg albuterol sulfate QID], and to Compare
      the preference/compliance of BID nebulization to QID use of MDI
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
